"title": "7786: shepherd, as king and leader",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7786",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Shepherd was a standard term for a leader or king throughout the ancient world. In this sense it often appears in the Bible.</p>\n<h2>General term for a king or leader</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:28\">ISA 44:28</a></strong> <em>The prophet describes this non-Jewish king as God's shepherd</em>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer6:3\">JER 6:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam7:7\">2SA 7:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps77:20\">PSA 77:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa31:4\">ISA 31:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer12:10\">JER 12:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer49:19\">JER 49:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer50:44\">JER 50:44</a></p>\n<h2>The LORD as shepherd</h2>\n<h3>Of Israel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps80:1\">PSA 80:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen49:24\">GEN 49:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps28:9\">PSA 28:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:11\">ISA 40:11</a></p>\n<h3>Of the individual</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps23:1\">PSA 23:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen48:15\">GEN 48:15</a></p>\n<h2>David as the model of a good shepherd</h2>\n<h3>Experience as a real shepherd</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:70-Ps78:71\">PSA 78:70–78:71</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:34-1Sam17:37\">1SA 17:34–17:37</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam12:1-2Sam12:7\">2SA 12:1–12:7</a> <em>The king is brought to his senses by a “shepherd” story</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps23:1-Ps23:4\">PSA 23:1–23:4</a></p>\n<h3>The shepherd faces death for his flock</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam24:17\">2SA 24:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:32\">EXO 32:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:11\">JHN 10:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:15\">JHN 10:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:17\">JHN 10:17</a></p>\n<h3>David as a model of the coming Messiah</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek34:23\">EZK 34:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:4-Jer23:5\">JER 23:4–23:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer30:9\">JER 30:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos3:5\">HOS 3:5</a></p>\n<h2>A good shepherd as a leader ``after God's own heart''</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer3:15\">JER 3:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:11\">ISA 40:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:10\">JER 31:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek34:12\">EZK 34:12</a></p>\n<h2>A bad shepherd</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs22:17\">1KI 22:17</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Criticisms of the shepherds of Israel</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:1-Jer23:2\">JER 23:1–23:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer10:21\">JER 10:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer22:21-Jer22:22\">JER 22:21–22:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek34:1-Ezek34:10\">EZK 34:1–34:10</a></p>",
